The result of potentiodynamic polarization graph is Tafel plots of ASTM A106 coating with polyurea and Copper nanoparticles in chloride medium the solution with a concentration of 3.5 wt.% sodium chloride medium as shown in Fig. 2
                        . X-axes represent the natural logarithm of corrosion current density in micro per ampere per centimeter square (icorr
                        ) and the y-axis represents corrosion potential (Ecorr
                        ). There are two samples S1 and S2. S1 is coated with pure polyurea and S2 is polyurea with 2 wt.% copper nanoparticles. Fig. 2. shows that by applying Copper nanoparticles as an additive in polyurea on the ASTM A106 samples, corrosion current density decreases while corrosion potential increases. Moreover, by comparing pure polyurea cure with S2 which has 2 wt.% copper nanoparticles it can be concluded that by adding copper nanoparticles graphs shift towards lower current and higher potential. Table 3
